<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/584.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Bishop <persName type="to">Brent</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-02-26"><hi rend="italic">February 26,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Bacon informs him that department is gratified with resolutions
                            passed by international commission, authorizes him to publish
                            resolutions, and compliments him on the successful termination of this
                            phase of his work.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>